  "text": "The type inference and method overload resolution pipeline in the Roslyn C# compiler is orchestrated through a chain of cooperating components in the src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/ directory structure.\n\nThe primary entry point is the OverloadResolution class (src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/OverloadResolution/OverloadResolution.cs), which contains three main public Resolve methods: ObjectCreationOverloadResolution (line 101), MethodInvocationOverloadResolution (line 135), and PropertyOverloadResolution (line 162). These methods coordinate the entire overload resolution process.\n\nThe OverloadResolution class is actually a partial class with a second partial definition in OverloadResolution_ArgsToParameters.cs that handles argument-to-parameter matching and candidate evaluation.\n\nKey components of the pipeline:\n\n1. **Type Inference**: The MethodTypeInferrer struct (MethodTypeInference.cs, line 91) performs generic type argument inference for parameterized methods. It processes bound expressions and method groups to infer type arguments when they are not explicitly provided. The inference follows the C# specification's algorithm for fixing type parameters based on input/output type inferences.\n\n2. **Overload Resolution**: After type inference, PerformMemberOverloadResolution applies conversion analysis and parameter matching. The BetterFunctionMember method (OverloadResolution.cs, lines 1951 and 1990) implements the comparison logic to determine which of two candidate methods is better, considering parameter accessibility, conversion quality, and method constraints.\n\n3. **Conversion Ranking**: The Conversions class (src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/Conversions/Conversions.cs, line 15) inherits from ConversionsBase and ranks implicit conversions for parameter matching. This is critical for determining which overload is best when multiple methods could apply to given arguments.\n\n4. **Best Type Inference**: The BestTypeInferrer static class (BestTypeInferrer.cs, line 14) provides InferBestType for array and conditional expressions, determining the common type of a set of expressions. This complements the generic method type inference by handling scenarios where the target type is implicit rather than derived from method parameters.\n\n5. **Result Structures**: Supporting data structures include OverloadResolutionResult<TMember>, MemberResolutionResult<TMember>, MemberAnalysisResult, and ArgumentAnalysisResult, which track the status and diagnostics of candidate methods through the resolution pipeline.\n\nThe pipeline integrates with the broader Binder system through files like Binder_Invocation.cs, which calls MethodInvocationOverloadResolution for method call expressions, and Binder_Operators.cs, which uses specialized operator overload resolution in BinaryOperatorOverloadResolution.cs and UnaryOperatorOverloadResolution.cs.\n\nThis architecture cleanly separates concerns: type inference determines generic arguments, overload resolution ranks candidates, conversion analysis supports parameter matching, and best type inference handles implicit typing scenarios. The BetterResult enum tracks comparison outcomes (Left, Right, Neither, Equal), allowing efficient elimination of suboptimal candidates."
}

